    • Class edu.regis.msse670.model.domain.Inventory extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      -874226773898054104L

      • Serialized Fields

        • name

          java.lang.String name
          The value is used as the primary identifier for the object and must be unique.

        • tier

          byte tier
          The value is used to determine in another inventory is allowed to be stored within the object. only objects with higher tier values are allowed to be stored. The exception is tier -1, which can be stored in any object but never accepts other objects for storage.

        • objectInventory

          java.util.ArrayList<E> objectInventory
          The ArrayList acts as 'storage' for other Inventory objects. The maximum number of stored objects is defined by inventoryMax and the current number of stored items is tracked by inventoryStored.

        • inventoryMax

          int inventoryMax
          Value sets the maximum stored objects. 0 allows no storage

        • inventoryStored

          int inventoryStored
          Value tracks number of currently stored objects
